  "title": "Full Stack Developer (React.JS/Node.JS/PHP, Marine)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Craft interactive and adaptable user interfaces using React.js features like hooks and state management tools, ensuring seamless user experiences.</li>\n  <li>Develop and maintain backend services and RESTful APIs with Node.js, Express, and PHP to support robust application functionality.</li>\n  <li>Architect efficient data models and optimize database queries for MongoDB, PostgreSQL, and MySQL environments.</li>\n  <li>Integrate and manage third-party APIs to extend application capabilities while collaborating effectively within an agile team setting.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Computer Science or equivalent</li>\n  <li>At least 4 years of practical experience in <strong>full stack development</strong> using <strong>React.js</strong>,<strong> Node.js</strong>, and <strong>PHP</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Strong proficiency in<strong> React.js, Node.js, PHP</strong>, and <strong>JavaScript/TypeScript </strong>following modern coding standards.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R21100996</p>",
